    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Certainly! Lasso (L1 regularization) and Ridge (L2 regularization) are both methods to prevent overfitting by adding a penalty to the coefficients of your model. Lasso tends to shrink some coefficients to zero, effectively performing feature selection, while Ridge keeps all coefficients but shrinks them towards zero. You might choose Lasso when you believe only a few features are important, whereas Ridge is better when you expect many features to be relevant.",
